-- Chinese Firm to Build Power Plant in Central Iran, Times Reports
-- B y   Y e g a n e h   S a l e h i
-- 2012-07-08T07:55:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-08/chinese-firm-to-build-power-plant-in-central-iran-times-reports.html
A Chinese company has invested some
$500 million for the construction of a coal-fired power plant in
central  Iran ,  Tehran Times  reported, citing Iranian Deputy
Energy Minister Mohammad Behzad.  Behzad, who didnâ€™t name the company, said the power plant
will be located in the city of Tabas in Yazd Province and will
be able to generate 650 megawatts of electricity.  The project requires a total of 7 trillion rials ($570
million) and is planned to start operating within six years,
Behzad said, according to the newspaper.  Iran has plans to generate 5,000 megawatts of electricity
through the use of coal-fired plants, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
